mourning%20the%20loss%20of%20my%20independence%2C%20something%20I%20fiercely%20protected%20for%20years.%20I%20had%20this%20new%2C%20adorable%20little%20human%20who%20was%20relying%20on%20me%20for%20everything%2C%20and%20it%20felt%20incredibly%20overwhelming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20my%20mind%20and%20body%20settled%20down%2C%20we%20found%20our%20groove%20in%20parenthood.%20And%20while%20things%20were%20different%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20it%20looked%20the%20same.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20decided%20that%20while%20our%20children%20would%20be%20our%20priority%2C%20it%20was%20important%20to%20weave%20them%20into%20our%20life%2C%20rather%20than%20orbiting%20around%20theirs.%20We%20wanted%20to%20expose%20them%20to%20the%20loves%20of%20our%20lives%20%E2%80%94%20traveling%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-ways-to-use-space-from-someone-living-on-sailboat-photos-2022%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esailing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20ocean%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20felt%20it%20important%20for%20them%20to%20recognize%20their%20parents%20had%20passions%2C%20too.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20pregnant%20with%20our%20second%20was%20a%20no-brainer.%20It%20was%20part%20of%20the%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f8d6f6eb-879f-418d-a71a-153de4f9d11c%5C%22%3EI%20immediately%20wanted%20a%20third%20child%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20the%20most%20unexpected%20thing%20happened.%20While%20I%20looked%20down%20at%20my%20second%20child%20as%20he%20peacefully%20took%20a%20milk-drunk%20newborn%20nap%20on%20my%20chest%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20wanted%20another%20one.%20This%20was%20most%20certainly%20not%20part%20of%20the%20plan.%20Thinking%20about%20having%20a%20third%20while%20I%20was%20freshly%20postpartum%20with%20my%20second%20felt%20absolutely%20unhinged.%20And%20absolutely%20right%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%20I%20would%20never%20have%20imagined%20taking%20a%20leave%20of%20absence%20from%20my%20career%20to%20focus%20on%20my%20family.%20But%20life%20felt%20off.%20I%20rushed%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20door%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20I%20rushed%20to%20pick%20them%20up%20from%20daycare%20after%20work%2C%20I%20rushed%20through%20dinner%20so%20they%20could%20get%20to%20bed%20on%20time.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20it%20felt%20good.%20And%20I%20was%20constantly%20left%20with%20the%20question%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20are%20we%20doing%3F%26quot%3B%20The%20more%20I%20discussed%20hitting%20the%20pause%20button%20on%20my%20career%2C%20the%20more%20it%20made%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20leave%20of%20absence%20allowed%20us%20to%20slow%20down%20the%20furious%20pace%20of%20our%20lives%20by%20breathing%20more%20time%20and%20space%20into%20our%20days.%20Things%20ran%20more%20smoothly.%20Suddenly%20there%20was%20time%20for%20making%20sprinkle%20pancakes%20on%20weekday%20mornings%20and%20space%20to%20read%20more%20than%20one%20book%20together%20before%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20I%20can't%20imagine%20returning%20to%20the%20workplace%20at%20all.%20I%20feel%20pulled%20to%20continue%20to%20focus%20on%20my%20family%2C%20as%20I'm%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20giving%20birth%20to%20a%20third%20baby%20I%20so%20clearly%20knew%20was%20meant%20to%20be%20part%20of%20our%20family.%20I%20couldn't%20be%20more%20excited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cb0e2da4-5182-47a7-8307-a97fc93ba26d%5C%22%3EWe%20should%20be%20flexible%20with%20our%20life%20plans%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tell%20my%20sons%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20always%20change%20your%20mind.%26quot%3B%20As%20adults%2C%20we%20need%20to%20remember%20this%20as%20well.%20It's%20important%20to%20approach%20life%20with%20forethought%20and%20plans%2C%20but%20equally%20important%20to%20approach%20it%20with%20a%20notion%20of%20flexibility%2C%20allowing%20ourselves%20the%20possibility%20of%20altering%20the%20game%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20should%20have%20goals%2C%20work%20furiously%20toward%20them%2C%20but%20allow%20ourselves%20the%20gift%20of%20changing%20our%20minds%20and%2