id%20he%20downloaded%20%26quot%3Bsensitive%20non-public%26quot%3B%20documents%20related%20to%20the%20FAA%20and%20took%20them%20to%20Iran%20in%20April%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20included%20documents%20related%20to%20the%20NAS%20that%20would%20give%20a%20person%20unfamiliar%20with%20NAS%20facility%20engineering%20a%20reasonable%20understanding%20of%20how%20the%20NAS%20power%20and%20electrical%20architecture%20is%20configured%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20DOJ%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20using%20a%20cover%20story%20%26quot%3Bbased%20on%20purported%20discussions%20about%20research%20with%20fellow%20academics%2C%26quot%3B%20Rahmati%20would%20also%20go%20on%20to%20obtain%20%26quot%3Bvarious%20non-public%20and%20open-source%20materials%20related%20to%20the%20US%20solar%20energy%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20he%20passed%20on%20to%20an%20Iranian%20government%20official%2C%20the%20DOJ%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERahmati%20sent%20further%20information%20about%20US%20solar%20energy%2C%20solar%20panels%2C%20the%20FAA%2C%20airports%2C%20and%20air%20traffic%20control%20towers%20to%20his%20brother%20in%20April%202022%2C%20it%20said%2C%20with%20his%20brother%20alleged%20to%20have%20acted%20as%20a%20middleman%20in%20sending%20files%20to%20Iranian%20intelligence%20on%20his%20behalf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobert%20Wells%2C%20the%20executive%20assistant%20director%20of%20the%20FBI's%20National%20Security%20Branch%2C%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20indictment%20describes%20the%20reprehensible%20actions%20of%20an%20individual%20who%20allegedly%20betrayed%20his%20country%20by%20transferring%20sensitive%20US%20information%20to%20a%20foreign%20power.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20alleged%20betrayal%20not%20only%20undermines%20our%20national%20security%20but%20also%20puts%20US%20jobs%20and%20livelihoods%20at%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DOJ%20and%20the%20Islamic%20Republic%20of%20Iran%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%