2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fgovt-considering-three-bills-to-implement-one-nation-one-election-plan-124092900359_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tonight%2C%20As%20India%20Sleeps%2C%20Earth%20Will%20Get%20A%20'Mini%20Moon'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Earth%20will%20embrace%20a%20new%20and%20temporary%20'mini%20moon'%20tonight%2C%20with%20a%20connection%20to%20India's%20epic%20Mahabharat.%20Called%20%26quot%3B2024%20PT5%26quot%3B%20it%20is%20just%20about%20ten%20meters%20in%20diameter%20and%20it%20will%20remain%20in%20the%20Earth's%20orbit%20for%20about%2053%20days%20before%20heading%20back%20into%20the%20vastness%20of%20the%20solar%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20size%2C%20though%2C%20makes%20it%20way%20too%20small%20to%20register%20--%20the%20diameter%20of%20the%20Moon%20is%203%2C476%20kilometres.%C2%A0%20The%20%26quot%3B2024%20PT5%26quot%3B%20is%20350%2C000%20times%20smaller%20and%20will%20not%20be%20visible%20to%20the%20naked%20eye.%20But%20special%20telescopes%20could%20well%20detect%20it%20well%20after%201.30%20am.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20naturally%20orbiting%20body%20around%20a%20planet%20is%20called%20a%20moon.%3Cbr%3E%5CnPlanet%20Saturn%20has%20146%20known%20moons%20and%20Jupiter%20has%2095.%20Mars%20has%20two%20moons%20and%20the%20Earth%20has%20just%20one%20Moon.%20Venus%20has%20no%20known%20moons.%3Cbr%3E%5CnExperts%20at%20ISRO%20monitoring%20%26quot%3B2024%20PT5%26quot%3B%20said%20it%20%26quot%3Bwould%20not%20collide%20with%20Earth%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECarlos%20de%20la%20Fuente%20Marcos%20and%20Ra%C3%BAl%20de%20la%20Fuente%20Marcos%20--%20the%20two%20scientists%20who%20reported%20it%20--%20said%20%26quot%3BNear-Earth%20Objects%20(NEOs)%20that%20follow%20horseshoe%20paths%2C%20and%20approach%20our%20planet%20at%20close%20range%20and%20low%20relative%20velocity%2C%20may%20undergo%20mini-moon%20events%20in%20which%20their%20geocentric%20energy%20becomes%20negative%20for%20hours%2C%20days%20or%20months%2C%20but%20without%20completing%20one%20revolution%20around%20Earth%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20object%20is%20too%20small%20and%20dim%20for%20typical%20amateur%20telescopes%20and%20binoculars.%20However%2C%20the%20object%20is%20well%20within%20the%20brightness%20range%20of%20typical%20telescopes%20used%20by%20professional%20astronomers%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Marcos%20said%20to%20US-based%20website%20space.com.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20telescope%20with%20a%20diameter%20of%20at%20least%2030%20inches%2C%20plus%20a%20CCD%20or%20CMOS%20detector%20is%20needed%20to%20observe%20this%20object%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3B2024%20PT%205%26quot%3B%20was%20discovered%20on%20August%207%2C%202024%20by%20the%20Asteroid%20Terrestrial-impact%20Last%20Alert%20System%20(ATLAS)%2C%20an%20automated%20system%20funded%20by%20NASA%20and%20run%20from%20Hawaii.%20It%20is%20used%20to%20monitor%20near-earth%20asteroids.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20space%20agency%20ISRO's%20sharp%20lookout%C2%A0%20--%20the%20Network%20for%20Space%20Objects%20Tracking%20and%20Analysis%20(NETRA)%20--%20is%20keeping%20an%20eye%20on%20the%20asteroid%2C%20which%20will%20disappear%20by%20November%2025%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Marcos%20said%20this%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20mini%20moons%20appear%20around%20the%20Earth.%20It%20happened%20in%201997%2C%202013%20and%202018.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuch%20orbital%20elements%20are%20consistent%20with%20those%20of%20the%20Arjunas%2C%20a%20sparsely%20resonant%20population%20of%20small%20NEOs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3BArjuna%26quot%3B%20scientists%20refer%20to%20is%20a%20unique%20group%20asteroids.%20The%20other%20group%20of%20asteroids%20in%20the%20solar%20system%20are%20Apollo%2C%20Atira%2C%20Amor%2C%20and%20Aten.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3B2024%20PT5%26quot%3B%20is%20supposed%20to%20have%20its%20origins%20in%20the%20Arjuna%20group%20and%20is%20expected%20to%20have%20a%20periodicity%20of%20a%20year.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20prolific%20discoverer%20of%20asteroids%20and%20comets%2C%20Astronomer%20Robert%20H%20McNaught%2C%20on%20November%201%2C%201991%2C%20discovered%20an%20asteroid%20%E2%80%93%20later%20named%20%26quot%3B1991%20VG%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20Siding%20Spring%20Observatory%20in%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20name%20%26quot%3BArjuna%26quot%3B%20was%20chosen%20by%20the%20discoverer%2C%20Mr%20McNaught%2C%20inspired%20by%20the%20Arjuna%2C%20a%20hero%20of%20the%20epic%20Mahabharata.%3Cbr%3E%5CnIn%20mythology%2C%20Arjuna%20is%20known%20for%20his%20bravery%2C%20archery%20skills%2C%20wisdom%20and%20spiritual%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20name%20reflects%20the%20asteroid's%2C%20swift%20passage%20through%20the%20solar%20system%20(like%20Arjuna's%20swift%20arrows)%3B%20unpredictable%20nature%20(like%20Arjuna's%20complex%20character).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Astronomical%20Union%20(IAU)%20officially%20approved%20the%20name%20for%20the%20asteroid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Anil%20Kumar%2C%20head%20of%20ISRO's%20Network%20for%20Space%20Objects%20Tracking%20and%20Analysis%20(NETRA)%2C%20confirmed%20the%20%26quot%3B2024%20PT5%26quot%3B%20is%20part%20of%20the%20Arjuna%20Asteroid%20grouping.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727606340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fttcehut_moon-generic-560_625x300_10_April_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F2024-pt5-moon-isro-nasa-tonight-as-india-sleeps-earth-will-get-a-mini-moon-6676679%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Earth%20will%20embrace%20a%20new%20and%20temporary%20'mini%20moon'%20tonight%2C%20with%20a%20connection%20to%20India's%20epic%20Mahabharat.%20Called%20%26quot%3B2024%20PT5%26quot%3B%20it%20is%20just%20about%20ten%20meters%20in%20diameter%20and%20it%20will%20remain%20in%20the%20Earth's%20orbit%20for%20about%2053%20days.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engag