0aeration.%20This%20is%20crucial%20for%20maintaining%20moisture%20and%20oxygen%20levels%20in%20the%20compost%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%20Aeration%20involves%20creating%20air%20pockets%20that%20allow%20enough%20oxygen%20to%20convert%20organic%20matter%20into%20compost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20collection%20and%20composting%20process%20is%20done%20manually.%20The%20sloping%20terrain%20is%20utilised%2C%20allowing%20waste%20to%20be%20placed%20at%20a%20facility%20uphill%20from%20where%20it%20gently%20rolls%20down%20to%20the%20composting%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EReviving%20a%20stream%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ve%20planted%20about%20600%20trees%20in%20the%20area%2C%E2%80%9D%20Utsow%20says%20when%20I%20ask%20him%20about%20the%20tiny%20river%20flowing%20through%20the%20compound.%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ve%20also%20cut%20the%20hills%20into%20steps%20to%20allow%20water%20to%20recharge%20the%20soil%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20river%2C%20like%20several%20others%20flowing%20in%20the%20Shivaliks%2C%20is%20most%20active%20during%20the%20monsoon%20season.%20It%20is%20mostly%20rain-fed%20and%20often%20acts%20as%20a%20tributary%20to%20glacier-fed%20rivers%20like%20the%20Teesta%20and%20Ganga.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20particular%20stream%20has%20become%20perennial%2C%20Snehal%20informs%20me%2C%20explaining%20that%20the%20abundant%20groundwater%20provides%20a%20constant%20flow.%20Members%20of%20the%20Tieedi%20team%20have%20also%20placed%20nets%20along%20the%20stream%E2%80%99s%20borders%20to%20prevent%20people%20from%20dumping%20garbage.%20An%20interesting%20technique%20they%20employ%20is%20setting%20up%20a%20small%20temple%20at%20a%20part%20of%20the%20stream.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTreating%20it%20as%20an%20auspicious%20site%20prevents%20locals%20from%20dumping%20garbage%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20Snehal%20explains.%20A%20tiny%20bamboo%20bridge%20connects%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20complex%