09%2Fhanif-kureshi-1727337833-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-367634%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20mural%20features%20in%20the%20Lodhi%20Art%20District%20of%20Delhi%2C%20painted%20by%20Saner%20Edgar.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTypefaces%20are%20like%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20once%20said.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20knew%20them%20by%20the%20clothes%20they%20wore.%20You%20could%20take%20Helvetica%20to%20a%20party%20and%20it%20would%20fit%20it%20%5Bin%5D%2C%20while%20the%20single%20font%2C%20red%20box%20of%20The%20Economist%20is%20so%20distinct.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrough%20the%20years%2C%20Kureshi%E2%80%99s%20work%20transcended%20the%20alleyways%20of%20Indian%20cities%20and%20moved%20across%20horizons.%20The%20colours%20of%20his%20legacy%20spilt%20onto%20the%20London%20Design%20Biennale%2C%20Venice%20Biennale%2C%20Centre%20Pompidou%20Paris%2C%20Triennale%20Design%20Museum%2C%20Milan%2C%20and%20Sikka%20Art%20Fair%20Dubai.%20His%20work%20was%20acclaimed%20by%20progressive%20artists%20for%20its%20depiction%20of%20life%20in%20its%20truest%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESt%2Bart%20India%20Foundation%3A%20Making%20art%20accessible%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20deep%20desire%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F335593%2Fpadma-shri-jagdish-and-kamla-mittal-museum-of-indian-art-hyderabad-indian-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etake%20art%20out%20of%20traditional%20galleries%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20make%20it%20accessible%2C%20a%20part%20of%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20DNA%20if%20you%20will%2C%20coloured%20each%20of%20Kureshi%E2%80%99s%20choices.%20He%20co-founded%20St%2Bart%20Foundation%20in%202013%20modelled%20on%20this%20belief.%20The%20not-for-profit%20organisation%20headquartered%20in%20Delhi%20saw%20Kureshi%2C%20Arjun%20Bahl%2C%20Akshat%20Nauriyal%